{"id":24,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":24,"title":"Chapter 21: The Amlicites","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 21"],["h1","The Amlicites"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p3"},"Amlici was a clever, wicked man who wanted to be king of the Nephites. He had many followers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.1-2"},"Alma 2:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p5"},"The righteous Nephites did not want Amlici to be their king. They knew he wanted to destroy God’s Church."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.3-4"},"Alma 2:3–4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p7"},"The Nephites gathered in various groups to decide if Amlici should be king. Most of the people voted against Amlici, and he did not become king."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.5-7"},"Alma 2:5–7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p9"},"Amlici and his followers became angry. They left the Nephites, made Amlici their king, and called themselves Amlicites. Amlici ordered them to fight the Nephites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.8-11"},"Alma 2:8–11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p11"},"The righteous Nephites prepared to defend themselves with bows and arrows, swords, and other weapons."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.12"},"Alma 2:12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p13"},"The Amlicites attacked, and the Nephites, who were led by Alma and strengthened by the Lord, killed many of them. The rest of the Amlicites ran away."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.15-19"},"Alma 2:15–19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p15"},"Alma sent spies to watch the Amlicites. The spies saw them join a large army of Lamanites and attack Nephites living near Zarahemla."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.21,24-25"},"Alma 2:21, 24–25"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p17"},"The Nephites prayed, and God helped them again. They killed many soldiers of the Lamanite-Amlicite army."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.28"},"Alma 2:28"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p19"},"Alma and Amlici fought each other with swords. Alma prayed that his life would be spared, and God gave him the strength to kill Amlici."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.29-31"},"Alma 2:29–31"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p21"},"The Nephites chased the Lamanites and Amlicites into the wilderness. Many of the wounded died there and were eaten by wild animals."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.36-38"},"Alma 2:36–38"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_024_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p23"},"Like the Lamanites, the Amlicites marked themselves with red, which fulfilled a prophecy. The Amlicites had separated themselves from the blessings of the gospel."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-21-the-amlicites.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/3.4,14,18-19"},"Alma 3:4, 14, 18–19"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
